U.S. Federal Reserve Chairman Ben S. Bernanke and European Central Bank President Mario Draghi each
will give speeches in the coming week.  Group of Seven central bank governors and finance ministers
will meet outside London for two days to discuss the state of
the global economy.  Pakistan will elect a new government. China will release
trade and inflation data for April, which may indicate whether
the second-largest economy is slowing.  News Corp. (NWSA) ,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , Walt Disney Co. and Toyota
Motor Corp. will be among companies releasing results.  MONDAY, MAY 6  To contact the reporters on this story:
